summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on Lebanon, particularly 425 (1978) and 426 (1978), 
Endorses the Secretary-General's report on UNIFIL and renews its mandate for six months until 31 January 2004; 
Reiterates support for Lebanon's territorial integrity, sovereignty, and political independence; 
Welcomes Lebanon's efforts to restore authority in the south and calls for continued measures to ensure a calm environment; 
Ensures UNIFIL's freedom of movement; 
Urges parties to respect the withdrawal line, exercise restraint, and cooperate with the UN and UNIFIL; 
Condemns violence and calls for an end to violations; 
Supports UNIFIL's efforts to maintain the ceasefire; 
Welcomes demining progress and encourages further assistance; 
Requests the Secretary-General to consult with Lebanon and report on implementation; 
Looks forward to UNIFIL's early fulfilment of its mandate; 
Stresses the need for a comprehensive, just, and lasting peace in the Middle East.
